a poem i hope moves you innocent little girls living in an oh so tainted world crayons and toys surviving amidst the threatening noise they remain one dreaming of knights secure in knowing what is right shields and armor enduring amidst the rancor they remain one aging without years grins streaking with tears boys and love denied by the one who stands above they remain one growing in fits and starts damaged without broken hearts to the world they go with grace and kindness to bestow they remain one spreading love all around their will alive and sound living apart but always together little girls of a feather they remain one firestarter is an idiot the meaning of it all was beautiful and saying the unity of the children after so much good and tragedy was great concept and it was true poetry i feel it was great and a devine and innocent approach it was simple yet it had such a good meaning stay strong Jon Secada One Tree Hill (TV series) Luminoth Scenes from a Memory Waking the Dragons Sin City Phaedo Pitaten John Berryman The Amber Spyglass The Beach Boys EastEnders Cliff Richard Kodocha Gosei Sentai Dairanger Queen (band) AFI 100 Years series Adam Mickiewicz W.I.T.C.H. Christmas Poetry Concepts in the Wheel of Time series William Shakespeare Slayer (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Salad Fingers Daredevil Faith (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Chicago (band) Karen Horney Love Tina Turner Alfred Edward Housman The 7th Guest Characters in Bleach series Torquato Tasso The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Shaggy dog story Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Batman Star Wars Episode VI: Return of the Jedi Characters of The Sandman The Dunciad Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Earth Girl Arjuna Care Bears Justification (theology) Duties of the Heart David Bowie Juliet Sex and the City Virginia Astley Marie Antoinette Link (Legend of Zelda) Divine grace Marilyn Monroe Girls Aloud His Dark Materials The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time characters Original sin American Idiot Blood on the Tr